snippet.textDisplay:
Well, that's good to hear. That you like other genres of music other than just metal. Bravo! As right you should. But there are so many others out there who don't. Perhaps like Glenn Fricker? Who seems to be the metalhead.

You are undoubtedly a stellar talent. But here I thought you were Korean? I get the impression you might not be? As I also know good kimchi from fake, kimchi. But I love all forms of Asian cuisine. I joke I think I used to be either Asian? Or maybe just a big fish? In a former life. As sushi is one of my favorite food groups. Followed by Chinese, Korean, Vietnamese, Thai food. But I don't discriminate. I'll eat any of that stuff daily.

Yeah... you're probably right about Glenn Fricker not having the time for you? And he is a busy boy. Even I had trouble getting him to respond to me. But also as an audio educator myself. Everything that he says on his videos. Is 100% right on. And I love the comic aspect especially. Like what those letters people write in with. Total dork' as most of them. Which is what makes them funny. I'm not even sure that he isn't just making that delirious stuff up? Though it does get the point across.

From an audio standpoint. You've got a great set up. You get great sound. You know what you're doing. And you do it so well. It would be my pleasure, if I ever get the chance to work with you. Which somehow I doubt? But ya never know? So... when are you coming to Austin, Texas? If you do? You really must look me up through my website of www.CROWmobile.com . I'd love to work with you. And then we can chow down on some Asian cuisine. While downing a bottle of sake. Ya think?

snippet.textDisplay:
Listening to Korean rock ballads ain't exactly my cup of tea. But Siegfried did a fabulous job here! I know you're a metal singer and quite a good one. Found out about you through Glenn Fricker's YouTube site.

Singing stuff like this is only going to make you better than the sum of your parts, already, Siegfried. It might even make you more money? It has a greater mass appeal beyond that of just metal lovers. 

Learn to sing like that in Spanish? And you'll become really popular in that other America we call South. And plenty in the USA as well. 

Even though I also don't speak nor understand Spanish or Korean. Being a true artist that you are Siegfried, is undeniable! You're fabulous! Now also learn, some Wagner and Mozart ? And you'll have it down! Dude. You can have it all! 

But who am I.? But just another one of those, 4 time, Major Music Award nominated Engineer/Producers. Here in the USA. And where I think, Glenn Fricker, is also doing a great job. For you/with you. Even if he is a Canadian. I mean how many hits have come out of Canada? I really can't Guess Who? 

Comedians like Glenn not so much so. We get plenty of comedians from Canada here in the USA. They're my favorite! So I have no idea why Glenn Fricker still lives in Ontario? I mean that's like Detroit. Kind of like living in Siberia. Though I've never lived there. How's the kimchi, in, Ontario, Canada? I like real Korean fermented kimchi. Ya know the stuff buried in your backyard. For a year. Where your dog poops all the time. Before you use him for dinner. Paired with the kimchi. And your singing.

Keep up the great work kid! You're fabulous! I'm not kidding. And Glenn Fricker makes you sound better than what you've posted yourself. Have Glenn, redo the soundtracks to your posts here at YouTube. I'm not even really anything more than a fan of Glenn Fricker. I've got a larger background and better equipment. And I know how superb, he is. He's right on with everything that he has said. In every one of his videos. It doesn't only pertain to metal. Then I wish he would widen his scope? Because he could do more than metal. You've also proved that to be true. With this ballad. That you've done here.

Ask Glenn Fricker to manage you. And to be your only recording producer and engineer. Sure I'd like to have that opportunity with you also. But you've already got a good working relationship with Glenn Fricker. And he's right on! You are gifted talent. So is he. Together, you'll both end up moving to Los Angeles. Otherwise you can keep freezing in Korea and he can keep freezing in Ontario. I prefer warmer climates like Austin, Texas and Los Angeles, California. As I'm from Detroit. And Washington DC. I love global warming! Everything grows better. Your pot plants will never die! I think you should do a lovely ballad? About your pot plants dying in the Korean winter time. It'll become a big hit here in the USA. You'll become a millionaire overnight. And then Glenn Fricker will be able to afford a Neve console like I have. And won't have to mix everything up with that digital bullshit.
